  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Janshruti (People\u2019s Voice) versus Union of India & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_4_2730_2735','2025INSC536'); ><font size='4'> <strong>JANSHRUTI (PEOPLE\u2019S VOICE)<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>UNION OF INDIA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2730</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 536</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007342025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SURYA KANT, N KOTISWAR SINGH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Directions sought for the formulation of gender-neutral guidelines and legislation governing the filing of domestic violence and harassment complaints. Also, sought declaration regarding the constitutionality of s.498A of the Penal Code, 1860 (now s.84 of 2023) Headnotes&dagger; Constitution of India &ndash; Art.32 &ndash; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.498A &ndash; Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 &ndash; s.84 &ndash; Whether the impugned provision i.e. s.498A of IPC warrant judicial interference: Held: No &ndash; This is so because it is<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> WRIT PETITION (CIVIL) No. 315/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_4_2730_2735','2025INSC536','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_4_2730_273